[The modern state of Cameroon was created in 1961 by the unification of 2 former colonies, 1 British and 1 French. Since then it has struggled from 1-party rule to a multi-party system in which the freedom of expression is severely limited. Cameroon began its independence with a bloody insurrection which was suppressed only with the help of French forces. Nonetheless, Cameroon saw investment in agriculture, education, health care and transport. Cameroon has 1 of the highest literacy rates in Africa. An interactive map HealthMap / ProMED-mail of Cameroon is available at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3536004,65. - Mod.CP]

