[5] Australia (Brisbane)
Date: 23 Jul 2015
Source: AAP [edited and abbreviated]
http://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/breaking-news/brisbane-braces-for-measles-outbreak/story-fni0xqi4-1227453458543


Brisbane residents are being warned to watch out for a measles outbreak after a student was diagnosed with the highly infectious illness.

The Taringa student was diagnosed after returning from a trip overseas and spent time at the airport, University of Queensland St Lucia campus and Indooroopilly Shopping Centre.

Initial symptoms include fever, a runny noise, moist cough and sore and red eyes.

